criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  the soft tissue defects involving the middle phalanx, the proximal interphalangeal
             joint, or both;

          -  a defect greater than or equal to 2 cm in length;

          -  a patient between 15 and 60 years of age.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  concomitant injuries to the dorsal skin of the middle phalanx of adjacent finger that
             precluded its use as donor site;

          -  injuries to the course of donor nerve branch;

          -  a defect less than 1.5 cm in length;

          -  a fingertip or pulp defect;

          -  a soft tissue defect of the thumb.
